blog.name: tryintoputitintowords
blog.title: 🦋
blog.description:
Taylor, when you think Argentina, I hope you think of me🦋
I was in 9th grade when I discovered this girl that told stories in every single one of her songs and had curly hair like me. There are 2 things I can talk about for hours non stop: Taylor Swift and Feminism. You can call me Cami and you should know Taylor and Ed make me very happy. I hope I get to hug them one day; in the mean time i will rejoice over their beautiful state-of-the-art songwriting and the way they make me feel with their music✨which is what got me to them and why i stayed 💘. Saw Ed live 3 times and those were some of the best nights of my life. Taylor follows (yes, i cried) so if you want help with anything let me know :) Soul crushingly waiting to see her live since 2009💘
I will not shut up about the fact that 19 year old Taylor swift wrote the entire Speak Now album by herself.
Also i often bitterpost about taylor not touring southamerica but its mainly because i don't understand the reason and it hurts.
Whether she releases 20 more albums or chooses the rose garden over Madison Square I will always love and support her because she brought so much light into my life for almost 10 years now✨❤

summary: “Other songs take a more serious tone - such as Who Cares , which addresses the brutality of internet bullying. "I was actually...
body:
“Other songs take a more serious tone - such as Who Cares , which addresses the brutality of internet bullying. “I was actually thinking about Taylor Swift and her relationship to her young fans and how it’s sort of a sisterly thing,” says Sir Paul of the song’s origins. And I was imagining talking to one of these young fans and saying, ‘Have you ever been bullied? Do you get bullied?’“

"Then I say, 'Who cares about the idiots? Who cares about all this? Who cares about you? Well… I do.’”



LIVING LEGEND PAUL MCCARTNEY A GODDAMN BEATLE WROTE A SONG ABOUT US @taylorswift I AM EMOTIONAL. THIS CANNOT BE REAL 😭😱😭
